The Nigerian entertainment industry is poised to honour Governor Ambode during the celebration of Lagos @50. According to a source in the know, the governor would be given as special position for his dynamism: “The Lagos @50 Celebration has fallen into two other events. While Lagos celebrates Lagos @50, the entertainment industry is also planning a grand launching and induction of deserving members into its Halls of Fame. A special position will be given to the amiable governor of Lagos State due to his dynamism as the grand patron of the Halls. “All these will be made possible by the Governor of Lagos State, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, the Federal Minister of Information & Culture and movie making legend, Eddie Ugbomah,” the source added. 